  "prompt": "What is the best way of combining multiple jpegs into one jpeg/PDF on Mac OS X?",
  "response": "Here are several methods to combine multiple JPEG images into a single PDF or JPEG on Mac OS X:\n\n1. Preview (Built-in Mac App):\n- Open the first image in Preview\n- Go to View > Thumbnails\n- Drag and drop other images into the sidebar\n- File > Export as PDF\n- Pros: Free, built-in, easy to use\n\n2. macOS Automator:\n- Open Automator\n- Create a new workflow\n- Choose \"Photos\" action\n- Add images\n- Export as PDF\n- Pros: Native, flexible\n\n3. Terminal Command (Quick):\n```bash\n# Combine PDFs\nconvert image1.jpg image2.jpg output.pdf\n\n# Combine JPEGs\nconvert image1.jpg image2.jpg +append output.jpg\n```\n- Requires ImageMagick (install via Homebrew)\n\n4. Third-Party Apps:\n- Adobe Acrobat\n- PDFElement\n- Pros: Professional features\n- Cons: Often paid\n\n5. Online Tools:\n- Google Docs\n- iLovePDF\n- Smallpdf\n- Pros: No installation\n- Cons: Privacy concerns, internet required\n\nRecommended: Preview or Automator for most users.",
